	<div itemprop="text"><p>I agree for the most part, but what would scare me if I was a commercial theme developer would be some actually reselling me theme at half price. The GPL gives them the right to take my work and profit from it without adding any value.  </p>
<p>I know you can&#8217;t stop pirates, but for that to be legal seems fundamentally wrong.</p>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
	<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/why-you-should-use-gpl-for-commercial-themes/comment-page-1/?replytocom=7664#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-7664", "7664", "respond", "455")'>Reply to this comment</a>	</div>
